events.name: Android Tools and Technologies Meetup
events.description:
GDG Bucharest starts a new series of technical meetups to bring together specialists, beginners and enthusiasts.

Stop by Thursday to talk about Android tools and technologies. Some of us will share their experience with some indispensable tools and talk about the way to use them when writing production code. 

Agenda:
- Catalin Morosan - “My Android Development Process”
- Victor Gradinescu - “Android Apps out in the wild”
- Informal discussions between members

Registration is free.

events.name: Google I/O - Developer Summary
events.description:
GDG Bucharest invites you to a new technical meeting regarding the newest updates of Google Products. We will talk about Android M, Material Design and other tools that may have got less public attention. Together, we’ll make a summary of the important things announced at Google I/O  and analyse their impact.

Do you have experience with Android Wear, Auto or TV? Well, we don’t… but we would like to understand better these platforms and the recent updates. If you think you can prepare a short presentation about them, let us know.

As we announced last time, we will have a peer-review session. If someone wishes to present to the community the product she has been working on (launched or soon to be) in order to get feedback, it’s possible. There will be a projector with Chromecast prepared to display Android devices. It’s a good opportunity to ask for support from the community, get feedback or just share your experience

Agenda:

Material Design - Updates and Showcase, Victor Gradinescu

Hangout with Marius Mailat - Google I/O 2015 from a developer perspective

Open discussion about Google I/O and the most recent updates

events.name: Android and The Rest of the World Meetup
events.description:
Dear fellow Google Hackers, 

It’s time to have a new meet-up focused on Android related technologies. For this one, we will meet in a new location, also suitable for some beer networking.

Agenda:

"Android and Bluetooth Low Energy", Rafalea Voiculescu

- Rafaela is the Android Team Lead at Vector Watch and she will share her experience and the challenges she encountered while interacting with BLE devices in Android Apps. Vector is a Romanian founded startup who has just launched their first generation of smartwatches, very well received worldwide.

"My code architecture for complex Android apps", Catalin Morosan - Makan Studios

- Catalin will talk about how to keep your sanity when dealing with gazillion screens, tens of API endpoints and constant client request changes.

Monthly roundup

This section will be about informal presentations, desktop sharing, live coding. Bring your laptop and show us an API you like, an app you’ve worked on or anything else you want to share with the community. Some of the already announced subjects are Android Auto, impressions from DroidCon London and Showcase: Mobile App for Unicef.

events.name: GDG Meetup - Green Wednesday
events.description:
Dear Android coders, join us on Wednesday, December 9th, for a "special offer" meetup about Android development. 

We'll go deeper into storing data on Android, reverse engineering and Android TV. We'll also talk about some competitions where we can exercise our skills.

Agenda:

• Diana Loredana Radu - "Benchmarking  Solutions for Storing Data in Android - Realm vs. Active Android vs Green Dao” 

• Mircea Nistor - "A first dive into reversing Android Apps"

• Victor Gradinescu - "Android and the TV”

events.name: Discover the GO Language and GCP Containers
events.description:
After several meetings on Android Development, our first meeting in 2016 will be almost all about the Backend. Please come to Tech Hub for this one, on the 6th of January, at 19:00.

The agenda will be:

• Florin Patan - The Go Programming language. 

Florin is co-organising GO language meetups as part of GDG Berlin and he’s also involved in the AWS community. He’s a maintainer of the GO plugin for the IntelliJ Platform.

He’ll introduce us to the Go language and talk about the benefits of using it vs other programming languages.

• Bogdan Nourescu - Containers & Google Cloud Platform

Bogdan is a Web App Developer with more than 5 years expertise in designing highly scalable apps. He is also a Google Cloud Platform Authorized Trainer

He’ll talk about what “containers" are, why are they the HOT topic of the day and how to start using them.

Until then we wish you “Craciun Fericit” and Happy Holidays!

events.name: ReactiveX in Action
events.description:
If you haven’t heard about ReactiveX by now, this meeting is the perfect opportunity to find all about it. No matter what programming language you’re using and no matter whether you are a front-end / back-end / web / mobile / desktop developer, this new way of writing code will make your programming life much easier.

Agenda:

“ReactiveX Basics” - Catalin Morosan

Catalin will give a broad overview of the main ReactiveX principles and concepts, independent of any particular programming language.

“ RxJava & RxAndroid -  Bringing ReactiveX to Android” - Cosmin Stefan-Dobrin

Cosmin will provide a quick introduction to using ReactiveX in Android development and will cover a few use-cases, showing how the paradigm can make app development easier and cleaner.  

“ReactiveX in the .NET world” - Costin Manda

Costin will showcase a dictionary lookup application comparing the standard coding approach to the ReactiveX approach.

This event will take place at Impact Hub, near Unirii.

events.name: Women Techmakers Romania
events.description:
We invite you to join the first event of Women Techmakers Romania community and to celebrate International Women’s Day. 

When: March 19th, 10:00 - 16:00

Where: Tech Hub Bucharest

Agenda:

* Intro about Community: Women Techmakers and GDGs

* Leader Experiences: The most of our speakers are girls! 

* Panel - You are a WOMAN. What's your SUPERPOWER?

* Start-ups Technical Challenge: WTM Let's Solve it!

We are finalizing information, so stay tuned for updates :)

Event is FREE, but registration is mandatory: http://goo.gl/forms/MeCxfwgn7n

Feel free to bring your colleagues (developers, designers, technology entrepreneurs), both women and men to our WTM event dedicated to the celebration of women achievements while calling for greater equality within our communities. This year’s theme is “Our Time To Lead”.

Partners: Google Developer Group Pitești - GDG Pitești, GDG Bucharest,Google Developer Group Cluj-Napoca l GDG Cluj, Atlas Networking,TechHub Bucharest

Women Techmakers is Google’s brand and global program with the goal to make women in tech more visible(www.womentechmakers.com).

events.name: IoT - The hardware revolution
events.description:
We can see a lot of innovation in Embedded Systems these days, from startups and big players alike. On a marked filled with awesome sensors, smart hubs and powerful hardware platforms Google is expected to deliver Brillo, it's IoT operating system that was announced last year. 

We finally take on this rich subject at a new GDG Bucharest meetup, at TechHub, on April 7th at 19:00.


Agenda:

• "Wireless Sensor Networks - Oportunities and Applications" - Dan Tudose

During the last decades, technology has enabled computing devices to become smaller and more specialised, which let an ever increasing number of systems that interact, improve and integrate in our everyday lives. A whole range of context aware applications has emerged which integrate the digital and physical worlds. Wireless Sensor Networks are the key to the new "ubiquitous computing" paradigm and should represent a new revolution in computer science, like the mainframes and the PCs were before them.

Dan holds a PhD in Computer Science and is the founder and coordinator Embedded Systems Laboratory and RoboLab from the Computer Science Faculty. He's passioned about everything related to hardware, embedded systems and robotics.

• "Open Hardware" - Rupert Whitehead (live on Hangout)

Rupert is a Developer Relations regional lead for UK and Ireland at Google. Prior to Google he worked at Nokia and Symbian before that (on the very first smartphones).

• "Brillo with Intel" - Andrei Dinu

Andrei is a Software Engineer working in the Brillo OS team in Intel. He's passionate about IOT and embedded systems, with experience on various operating systems. In his presentation he will showcase some of the solutions that can be built with Brillo.

events.name: Google IO 2016 - Developer Summary
events.description:
Join us on June 9th at TechHub for a post-I/O meeting where we will discuss all the main things from this year’s Google I/O conference.

We will try to cover all the major advancements in Google technologies:

• what is new in Android N and Android Tools

• Firebase

• Project Tango

• VR

• Progressive WebApps

• Cloud

… along with stories from people actually attending the conference.

Don’t forget to watch as much streamed content as possible from Google IO, starting with May 18th, and get ready to debate it with us.

events.name: Beer Night
events.description: Let's talk over a beer about what else we code, football and holidays. We'll take this opportunity to get to know each other better.

events.name: Summer Daydreaming - Intro to VR
events.description:
There has been an explosion of news on Virtual and Augmented Reality in the past year, with many devices and products being launched each week. In this meetup we’re going to take a deeper dive into Google’s stack for VR: Daydream, and we’re going to look at it from a technical as well as a conceptual/psychological/UX point of view.

Join us for this one on Tuesday, Aug 23rd, on the usual playground at TechHub.

Agenda

• "Daydream - Google VR  |  Build a simple VR experience with Unity3D” - Ovidiu Gheorghe, Ubisoft

Ovidiu Gheorghe is a VR Producer for Ubisoft here in Romania and he’s going to talk about the lessons his team learned while developing for Daydream, the tools they use in their creative process and why they use it. You’re going to see some live action as Ovidiu is taking us through their VR build process and maybe get a chance to play with a Daydream dev kit.

• “AR/VR and what it takes to design for human interaction” - Catalina Banuleasa, Tudor Juravlea

Besides scene rendering and audio latency, VR brings us a whole new set of issues regarding the user experience or the sense of immersion, which we’re going to address in this talk.

Catalina and Tudor are long time members of our community and have a rich experience in designing the user experience for various types of digital products. Cătălina is the User Experience Architect behind ING's Home'Bank internet and mobile banking platform. Tudor has had an important role in innovative projects (mobile, web, IoT) launched by big companies in Romania such as Orange, ING, Vodafone or E.ON. Both of them are also often mentoring startups and entrepreneurs on UX and they have recently started as UX Trainers for Scoala Informala de IT.

events.name: UX Tools for Mobile Apps
events.description:
La multi ani to all of you hackers out there! We suggest this first meeting for 2017 to discuss various tools for designing, prototyping and validating mobile apps. The lean startup, "release early release often" methodology has been with us for several years but now it’s all about validating ideas before building them, using high fidelity prototypes and tweaking that great user experience.

A huge number of tools exist out there for various stages of the design process, and some of them have been adopted not only by designers, but also by developers, as a common language.

Do you want to build a product in 2017? Hopefully we’ll get together on track with this meeting.

Agenda:

• Sketch, Pixate, Origami & tools that connect developers & designers better. 

Tools for Micro UX or Macro UX compared

Crowdsourced tips & tricks (tell us about your design process or your favourite tools)

• "Prototyping Mindset, Tools and Demos" - Nelson Vasconcelos, GDE UX (live through Hangouts)

Nelson is a passionate UI/UX Designer currently leading the mobile design at Youse, the largest brazilian insurtech. Google UI/UX Expert and Design Sprint Master, speaks for startups and developers about UX, Material Design and Design Sprint.

• Carmen Ruse, Adobe - Designing the next design tools

Carmen is going to talk to us about the design process behind building one of Adobe's new design tools.

Carmen went from architecture to the User Experience Design field, guided by the passion to create products that people value. She is currently one of the designers building Adobe Experience Design, the newest design and prototyping tool build for UX professionals.

events.name: IoT Things

venue.name: Facultatea de Automatica si Calculatoare, Universitatea Politehnica Bucuresti

events.description:
Hello hackers, we’ve prepared a series of IoT related events! There are lots of things happening in this space: new products, new platforms and new APIs. We’re hoping that through these events you’ll be able to develop new exciting products and continue to innovate.

Join us for this meetup in the new PRECIS building of the Faculty of Automatic Control and Computers, University Politehnica Bucharest.

Agenda:

• Rafaela Voiculescu - Senior Software Engineer, Fitbit

Rafaela has been trying the newly launched Android Things platform from Google. She will present an overview of Google's take on operating systems for low power IoT devices and the opportunities it brings.

• Bogdan Doinea - IoT Systems Engineer, Cisco

Join Bogdan in a session open to anyone interested in understanding the market, technical architectures, standards and entrepreneurship opportunities. The term "IoT" suffered from a lot of buzzwording, but it also produced important technological movements in most major business ecosystems, from agriculture and smart city to oil&gas, smart grid and transportation. Bogdan's presentation lies between business and technical, analyzing architectures, from connecting industrial machinery to the network, wireless sensor networks and edge storage to AEP platforms and real-time analysis, identifying key players at each step. The beauty of IoT is that it is such a vast field that it needs the collaboration of different companies with different technologies in order to produce a business outcome.

• Andrei Voinescu - CTO, Woogie

Aliens by Daria is romanian hardware startup building Woogie, a voice-activated AI-based learning companion for kids. Andrei will give us a look into what it means to build a voice-activated IoT device with a strong network connection.
events.how_to_find_us: Amfiteatrul PR001 din cladirea PRECIS (cladirea noua)

events.name: Workshop: Tensorflow and deep learning, without a PhD
events.description:
“Artificial Intelligence first” pare sa fie noul "Mobile First” :). Interesul pentru machine learning este urias iar plaja de tooluri si platforme a crescut foarte mult dar pentru a putea sa le folosim cu succes este necesar sa intelegem teoria si conceptele ce stau la baza Machine Learning.

Va invitam la un workshop introductiv de tensorflow si deep learning. Ii vom avea invitati pe Stefan Ruseti si Traian Rebedea de la Universitatea Politehnica din Bucuresti care ne vor indruma in completarea codelabului oferit de Google pentru lucrul cu Tensorflow si Neural Networks.

Pentru a participa la acest workshop trebuie sa veniti cu laptopul propriu, avand instalat

- Python (v3 recomandat)

- tensorflow

- matplotlib

- pentru a gestiona usor pachetele de python recomandam folosirea Anaconda

Instructiuni pentru configurarea mediului de lucru gasiti aici:

https://github.com/martin-gorner/tensorflow-mnist-tutorial/blob/master/INSTALL.txt

Cateva resurse utile pentru pregatirea workshopului:

- O introducere in Python pentru Data Science http://www.scipy-lectures.org/intro/index.html

- Cateva cheatsheets pentru a va reimprospata notiunile de:

algebra liniara: http://www.souravsengupta.com/cds2016/lectures/Savov_Notes.pdf

analiza: http://tutorial.math.lamar.edu/pdf/Calculus_Cheat_Sheet_All.pdf

statistica: http://web.mit.edu/~csvoss/Public/usabo/stats_handout.pdf

Alte resurse utile:

- http://neuralnetworksanddeeplearning.com/ - carte online de Michael Nielsen despre Retele Neurale cu demonstratii si vizualizari

- Machine Learning Content Bundle 2017 (Google) https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Cbh6cmzU4jYcF9Wawhy0fGJxjBJoPQ19U6-d9BzMaN0

Happy Coding!

events.name: I/O Extended 2017 Bucharest - Developer Summary
events.description:
Google IO is happening between May 17th and May 19th.
We invite you to a summary meetup on May 30th when we'll have a panel with our members attending IO in Mountain View this year. 

We'll try to cover everything new in Android, Daydream and Project Tango, Google Cloud Platform and Firebase, Android Things, Tensorflow and Deep Learning.

events.name: VR Jam at Dracula's Castle
events.description:
Developers, hackers, enthusiasts, artists and engineers are invited to work with each other, create, learn and explore Virtual Reality, Augmented Reality and 360 Video applications at our first VR event: VR Jam at Dracula’s Castle. We hope you would join us on the weekend of July 21-23 in Bran so we can envision historic, educational and touristic immersive experiences together and make them a reality.

More details here: https://www.facebook.com/events/1894306004142519

events.name: Develop for Virtual and Augmented Reality
events.description:
We begin the autumn meetups with a session dedicated to VR/AR development. Apple and Google have raced this year to add AR capabilities to iOS and Android. Likewise, VR has been growing steadily in adoption across a full range of domains.

We're going to see what it takes to build good experiences for these platforms and how to do it.

Agenda:

• George Cretu - "VR UX best practices across platforms"
George is an experienced VR developer and he's going to share his experience regarding UX patterns on Web, Mobile and Tethered VR. Implementation details are based on Unreal Engine or ReactVR.

• Ciprian Facaeru - "AR Space design & development"
Ciprian has been building awesome projects with both ARKit and ARCore. He's going to share some of his thoughts on good UX for AR and discuss the APIs in terms of capabilities and challenges.

events.name: Android Session
events.description:
A lot has happened on Android this year and it's time to get some updates on our favourite platform.

Agenda:

• An Architecture-First approach to building apps - Cosmin Stefan

An opinionated view on building sturdy, testable and scalable Android apps using the right architecture, based on MVVM, RxJava and DataBinding. We'll go into the details of our tried and tested approach to creating apps, from how data gets loaded and persisted to how it's prepared for the UI and how layouts are built, with a focus on how everything fits together.

• Looking over the Google I/O app source code - Victor Gradinescu

Each year Google releases the source code of the Google I/O app, that is used by its visitors and remote followers. In this hands-on session we'll dive into the code, look for good takeaways regarding architecture, interface, build management and study the integration with Firebase.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
• What we'll do
We start the new year with a resolution to learn about containers and orchestration in the cloud. This is the first event in a series of events on this theme and will be an introductory one.

So, want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?
Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Docker, Kubernetes and Scientific Data Processing, which will earn you additional badges.
Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $70+ value, free of charge.

Agenda:
18:30: Three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs
19:45: Break
20:00: Intro to Docker or Scientific Data Processing lab
21:00: Event ends

• What to bring
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

• Important to know

events.name: Android - Build to Scale
events.description:
The first Android meetup of the year is here. We'll be discussing advanced Android engineering with Doug Sillars ( http://dougsillars.com ), Principal Architect for Mobile Performance at AT&T, book author ( http://bit.ly/HighPerfAndroidApps ) and digital nomad. In the second part of the meetup we'll crowdsource the latest Android related tips and tricks.

Agenda:
- Doug Sillars - It's Time to Stop Stalling
Doug will speak about how the network calls in your mobile app can lead to poorly performing video and mobile applications. He'll walk through tools used for benchmarking web and native performance, and how to identify issues that may be slowing down your app. He will walk through issues seen in top mobile applications, how they were resolved, and how you as a developer can avoid the pitfalls that many top applications have suffered through.

By the end of the talk, you'll have an understanding of why network performance is a critical testing step to ensure an excellent customer experience, and will have a solid background on common issues that can be fixed.

- AdHoc Community Tips & Tricks Have you recently found a nice piece of Android code? A cool Android library? Maybe some hot tricks in Android Studio? Share your screen with us in this Lighting "5 minutes Talks" Session. Make sure you take a note each time you do something interesting this week.

SPONSORS ARE WELCOME: Do you have a message, product or service for the Google Developer Group? Power up this meetup, have your voice heard and your contribution will help us do even more cool stuff for the community.

events.name: Google HashCode - Bucharest 2018

venue.name: Facultatea de Automatica si Calculatoare, Universitatea Politehnica Bucuresti

events.description:
• What we'll do
Joi, 1 martie 2018, începând cu ora 19.00, se va desfășura competiția online Google HashCode, la Facultatea de Automatica si Calculatoare din cadrul Universității Politehnica din București, sala ED422.

Pentru a putea participa este necesar să faci parte dintr-o echipă. Înregistrarea individuală a fiecăruia dintre cei 2-4 membri ai unei echipe este deschisă până la data de 26 februarie 2018 ora 18:00 CET pe site-ul: https://hashcode.withgoogle.com/ HashCode este o competiție globală de programare între toate echipele înscrise în concurs, organizată anul acesta pentru a 5-a oară de către Google, în două etape:
- etapa de calificare online se va desfășura în ziua de 1 martie 2018, în intervalul orar 19:00 – 23:30, la hub-ul din cadrul campusului UPB https://goo.gl/c8A7Au
- etapa finală se va desfășura în ziua de 28 aprilie 2018, la sediul Google din Dublin.

Cine poate participa?
Sunt așteptați să participe studenți (de orice nivel) și / sau profesioniști în domeniul IT sau un domeniu corelat (Informatică, Informatică Economică, Matematică, Automatizări și Calculatoare, Telecomunicații etc.)

Unde mă înregistrez?
Înregistrarea oficială pe site-ul https://hashcode.withgoogle.com/ este obligatorie pentru cei ce doresc să participe.

Pentru mai multe detalii despre eveniment urmăriți paginile noastre de Facebook (GDG Bucharest și GDG Pitești), contactați organizatorii la adresa de email [masked] sau urmăriți pagina oficială https://hashcode.withgoogle.com/ Pe curând!

• What to bring

• Important to know
Înregistrarea oficială pe site-ul https://hashcode.withgoogle.com/ este obligatorie pentru cei ce doresc să participe.

events.name: I/O Extended Bucharest 2018 - Developer Summary
events.description:
We're going to discuss the latest news and releases from this year's I/O with the help of our colleagues present at the event.

Agenda:

19:00 - 20:00 - Android, Dev Tools, Flutter & Material Design - Cosmin Stefan, Valerica Plesu, Magda Miu, Victor Gradinescu

20:00 - 21:00 - Machine Learning, Actions and Bots - Traian Rebedea, Stefan Malnici, Cosmin Stefan, Victor Gradinescu

events.name: Android Summer Vibes
events.description:
It's been a while since we've had an event dedicated to Android, so we've decided to make up for it in style. This time, in a special location.

Agenda:
18:45 - 19:00: Arrivals & Registration

19:00 - 19:05: Welcome

19:05 - 19:50: Android Interface Definition Language (AIDL) When, Why and How? - Cristian Ichimescu
This presentation is about android Inter Process Communication with an incline to AIDL. It will describe some scenarios when using AIDL is suitable, with its benefits and downsides. It will also contain an example on how to implement them and a demo project.

19:50 - 20:10: Pizza & Beers

20:10 - 20:30: Quick walkthrough of some of the latest developments in the framework - Cosmin Stefan
During this demo we'll go through some of the latest additions of the Android framework, emphasising what can they do for you.

events.name: Running and Growing live apps with Firebase
events.description:
We begin the autumn Meetups season with a session dedicated to Firebase. The platform has been growing fast and Google is pushing it forward more and more.

In this edition we have invited a special guest (Jon Mensing, Product Manager at Google), to show us some of the lesser known features of Firebase that can make our lives easier during development and release.

Agenda:

18:45 - 19:00: Arrivals & Registration

19:00 - 19:05: Welcome

19:05 - 20:05: Running and Growing live apps with Firebase - Jon Mensing
You may be familiar with Firebase as a realtime database in the Cloud, but it's much, much more. In this session we'll discuss how Firebase can be used to improve your live app's quality, manage feature rollouts, perform A/B tests, send notifications, and more.

Jon Mensing is a Product Manager at Google who focuses on messaging and testing features within Firebase. His past experience includes work at BuzzFeed and Zynga. Jon has an MBA from Wharton, a Master of Public Policy degree from the Harvard Kennedy School, and a B.S. in Computer Science from the U.S. Air Force Academy.

20:05 - 21:00: Networking and discussions on Firebase and more

events.name: DevFest Romania 2018
events.description:
GDG DevFest Romania is happening in less then 2 weeks. We've got Googlers, Google Developer Experts and Industry Professionals who will present the latest technologies on 3 different tracks:
- Android & Kotlin
- Flutter, UX & Assistent
- Cloud & Data Engineering

Tickets and more details here: https://devfest.ro/

GDG DevFests are large, community-run developer events happening around the globe focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies.

GDG DevFest Romania is a community event, made by community for community. The main purpose of this conference is to bring together tech specialists and give to the attendees the possibility to participate at their presentations and ask them questions about their common passions: technology and programming.

events.name: GDG Garage - Build your product
events.description:
GDG Garage Series of Meetups is about working on side projects that you always wanted to do or finding real projects that provide a good opportunity for learning.

Starting March 5th we will meet once every three weeks in a hands-on atmosphere with the goal of launching new apps on the market (hopefully by late June).

In the first meetups we will define projects and teams, gather some early feedback. As we progress we will focus more on design, development, testing, marketing, post-release strategies. Each meetup will have a section dedicated for quick informal presentations or desktop sharing and an area for the teams to work.

The projects should be mostly related to Android (Mobile) or Google Assistant (chatbots, conversational interfaces) to make the most out of the community’s experience.

This is your chance to:
- get the help and the team to build the project you've been thinking of;
- exchange practical knowledge with experienced developers;
- be part of an active network of product builders.

We hope you are excited as we are and motivated to launch your (maybe first) product in 2019. Gather your team, write down your best idea and see you on March 5th.

events.name: Challenge Accepted Hackathon
events.description:
Va invitam la Challenge Accepted Hackathon unde vom lucra prototipuri de aplicații moderne, pentru soluționarea unor probleme stringente ale societății.

ÎMPREUNĂ, SCHIMBĂM LUMEA PRINTR-O LINIE DE COD!

Timp de 3 zile, în perioada 7-8-9 iunie, la București, lucrăm împreună pentru a găsi soluții simple la probleme complexe.

Soluțiile se vor baza pe tehnologii moderne și ar putea avea un impact pozitiv uriaș asupra vieții oamenilor.
Selectam probleme din sfera serviciilor medicale, pharma, servicii sociale si situatii de urgenta.

Cele mai importante 25 de idei sau prototipuri selectate de juriu și organizatori vor intra într-o perioadă de 100 de zile de incubare. Prototipurile se pot transforma în produse, dezvoltate, testate cu utilizatori reali și validate pentru implementare.

Proiectele care vor depăși stadiul de incubare au șanse reale să fie transformate în produse și să servească cauza pentru care au fost create. Este posibil ca unele proiecte să aibă nevoie de o perioadă mai mare pentru implementare.

Implică-te în eveniment și hai să schimbăm lumea împreună!

Înscrierile sunt deschise pe site-ul evenimentului:
www.challenge.scoalainformala.ro - la Scoala informala de IT - Bucuresti.

events.name: I/O Extended Bucharest 2019
events.description:
Google I/O 2019 has recently ended and quite a few announcements have been made. Join us for the I/O Extended Bucharest event, where we'll be going over the latest news and releases from this year's I/O with the help of some of the members of our community that were present at the event. Of course, we'll also have some SWAG for active participants!

We'll be going over the latest announcements regarding Android, Kotlin, Machine Learning, Flutter, Google Assistant and others.

Agenda:
19:00 - 20:30 - Panel discussion with speakers

events.name: Let's play with DIY AI Kits
events.description:
This event is dedicated to students.

We will play with DIY AI Kits from Google to test simple (or not) voice and vision AI models. If your passionate about electronics and AI don't miss this event.

The AIY Vision Kit from Google lets you build your own intelligent camera that can see and recognize objects using machine learning. All of this fits in a handy little cardboard cube, powered by a Raspberry Pi.

The AIY Voice Kit from Google lets you build your own natural language processor and connect it to the Google Assistant or Cloud Speech-to-Text service, allowing you to ask questions and issue voice commands to your programs. All of this fits in a handy little cardboard cube, powered by a Raspberry Pi.

events.name: Deep Dive into Firebase with Firebase Team
events.description:
We're excited to welcome you to an exciting event on the topic of Firebase, with 2 special guests that are part of the Firebase Team, joining us directly from the Firebase Summit.

Firebase is Google's mobile platform that helps developers and product teams quickly develop high-quality apps and grow their business. During this event, we'll cover some exciting topics and we'll get exciting insights and tips from members of the Firebase team. And, since it's following the Summit, we'll have the chance to find out more about the latest news related to the platform.

The event will be take place at the Avira Offices, who have been kind enough to host us for the evening.

events.name: DevFest Bucharest 2019
events.description:
We’re excited to announce DevFest Bucharest 2019!

This is a community-run, one-day conference aimed to bring developers, tech-companies, students and awesome speakers together in one location, so they can learn and share knowledge about established or emerging technologies on topics such as Cloud, Kubernetes, Big Data, Data science, Android, Flutter, Firebase, Mobile Technologies, Google Assistant, Machine Learning, Kotlin and more.

At GDG DevFest Bucharest 2019 our tracks will be: Android & Mobile Technologies, Kotlin/Everywhere and Cloud Technologies.

Read more and grab your tickets on: https://devfest.ro

AGENDA:
9:00 AM Registration & Welcome Coffee
10:00 AM Opening Keynote
10:30 AM Sessions
12:30 PM Lunch time
2:00 PM Sessions
6:30 PM Closing

GDG DevFest Bucharest is a community event, made by the community for the community. The main purpose of this conference is to bring together tech specialists and give to the attendees the possibility to participate in their presentations and ask them questions about their common passions: technology and programming.

group_profile.intro: Cosmin is a full-stack software engineer and leads the team that develops apps at the company he founded. With more than 7 years of experience in Android development, he believes great architecture and clean code are a must for an excelling product.

organizers.name: Victor G.
organizers.bio: I am a co-organiser of GDG Bucharest and have been involved in the tech community for over four years. In 2011 I co-founded Mobile Kinetics where my team focuses on native mobile applications on all major platforms, consumer or enterprise oriented.

group_profile.intro: As an entrepreneur since the early versions of iPhone and Android, I’ve been developing many native Mobile Apps, either consumer or enterprise oriented. I also build Enterprise Web Apps and did research in Vehicular Computing.
